<h2 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-3.0ProposedFutureStateArchitecture">3.0 Proposed Future Sta=
te Architecture</h2>
<h3 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-3.1GuidingPrinciples">3.1 Guiding Principles</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><em>Security First:</em> Implement the principle of least privilege for =
all access.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Traceability:</em> Ensure every change is version-controlled and aud=
itable.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Automation:</em> Automate promotions and repetitive tasks to reduce =
errors and increase velocity.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Separation:</em> Enforce strict separation between production and no=
n-production environments, duties, and data.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Atomicity:</em> Promote application changes as a single, consistent,=
 versioned unit to ensure stability.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-3.2ProposedSolutions">3.2 Proposed Solutions</h3>
<h4 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-3.2.1.FileShareandPermissionsArchitecture">3.2.1. File Shar=
e and Permissions Architecture</h4>
<p>A structured file share with Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) will be im=
plemented to segregate environments and enforce least privilege.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><em>Structure:</em></p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">\pfil\*=
\FileShares

=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 LoanAutomation-Prod/
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 LoanAutomation-UAT/
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 LoanAutomation-Staging/
=E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 LoanAutomation-Dev/
=E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 LoanAutomation-Archive/
  =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 2025-08-04_143000_Release-1.2.1/
    =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 manifest.json
    =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 Launcher-v1.5.exe
    =E2=94=9C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 LoanApplication.xlsm
    =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80 RiskAnalysis.accdb</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><em>Permissions Model:</em> New AD groups will be created to enforce sep=
aration of duties.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><em>Developers:</em> <code>Read/Write</code> access to <code>Dev</code> =
and <code>Staging</code>. <code>Read-only</code> to <code>UAT</code>. <stro=
ng>NO</strong> write access to <code>Prod</code> or <code>Archive</code>.</=
p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Application Support:</em> <code>Read/Write</code> access to all envi=
ronments, including the <code>Archive</code>, to manage promotions. They ar=
e the only group with <code>Write</code> access to <code>UAT</code>, <code>=
Prod</code>, and <code>Archive</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Business Users:</em> <code>Read-only</code> access to <code>Prod</co=
de> for execution. <code>Read-only</code> to <code>UAT</code> for testing.<=
/p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><em>Architect's Note on Permissions for MS Access Lock Files:</em><br>
An investigation was conducted into providing developers with a granular pe=
rmission set that would allow them to create MS Access lock files (<code>.l=
db</code>, <code>.laccdb</code>) in a read-only production directory withou=
t granting broader write access.</p>
<p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> This is not feasible with standard NTFS per=
missions. The architecturally sound solution is to provide a fully separate=
 <code>Dev</code> environment where developers have the necessary permissio=
ns to work effectively, eliminating any need for write access to the produc=
tion directory.</p>
</blockquote>
<h4 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-3.2.2.ImplementationStrategy:ParallelEnvironmentCutover">3.=
2.2. Implementation Strategy: Parallel Environment Cutover</h4>
<p>Recognizing that the proposed changes will impact the development team's=
 workflow, a parallel implementation strategy is recommended.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The new, structured file shares will be created in parallel to the exist=
ing legacy share.</p></li>
<li>
<p>A defined cutover period will be provided for the development team to tr=
ansition their workflows to the new <code>Dev</code> environment.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The Application Support team will simultaneously build and test promotio=
n automation using the new structure.</p></li>
<li>
<p>After the cutover period, the legacy file share will be set to read-only=
 and eventually decommissioned.</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-3.2.3.VersionControlStrategy(SourceCode)">3.2.3. Version Co=
ntrol Strategy (Source Code)</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p><em>Tool:</em> Enterprise GitHub.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Target:</em> All text-based source code, primarily the code for the =
"Launcher" application.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Branching Model:</em> A simple GitFlow model (<code>main</code>, <co=
de>develop</code>, <code>feature/*</code>) is recommended.</p></li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><em><span data-colorid=3D"jzjfp8jeav">Clarifying Question:</span></em><s=
pan data-colorid=3D"rabokghbcp"> Does the Launcher application contain any =
logic that is dependent on a specific version of an Access/Excel artifact?<=
/span></p>
<p><em><span data-colorid=3D"vwec8faoe4">Impact if False:</span></em><span =
data-colorid=3D"ef65ck8m3l"> If the Launcher and artifacts are tightly coup=
led, our release manifest becomes even more critical. We must ensure that a=
 change to the Launcher code cannot be deployed without the correct corresp=
onding artifact version, and vice versa.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<h4 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-3.2.4.DataManagementandSanitization">3.2.4. Data Management=
 and Sanitization</h4>
<p>A formal, automated process for creating safe, non-production datasets i=
s required.</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><em>Identify PII:</em> Conduct data discovery on the production database=
 to classify sensitive data.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Develop Scripts:</em> Create automated scripts to extract data from =
production.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Sanitize/Mask:</em> The scripts will mask, anonymize, or replace all=
 PII according to compliance requirements.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Load into Non-Prod:</em> The sanitized data will be loaded into the =
<code>Dev</code>, <code>Staging</code>, and <code>UAT</code> database envir=
onments.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Automate:</em> This entire process will be automated and scheduled t=
o ensure non-prod environments have recent but safe data.</p></li>
</ol>
<h4 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-3.2.5.ReleaseManagementandManifest(BinaryArtifacts)">3.2.5.=
 Release Management and Manifest (Binary Artifacts)</h4>
<p>To manage the reality that individual Access/Excel artifacts may be prom=
oted independently, a manifest-driven release process will be implemented. =
This ensures that even individual promotions are done in a controlled, atom=
ic, and traceable manner.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>The Release Package:</strong> A release is no longer a single fi=
le, but a "package" defined by a manifest. This package represents the comp=
lete, known-good state of the application for a given version.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>The Manifest:</strong> This is a simple file (e.g., <code>manife=
st.json</code>) created by Application Support in collaboration with the re=
questing developer. It explicitly lists every component and its specific ve=
rsion for that release.</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">  {
    "releaseId": "2025-08-04_143000_Release-1.2.1",
    "launcherVersion": "1.5",
    "launcherGitTag": "v1.5-release",
    "artifacts": [
      "LoanApplication.xlsm",
      "RiskAnalysis.accdb",
      "Reporting.xlsm"
    ]
  }</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-4.0Assumptions&amp;RequiredClarifications">4.0 Assumptions =
&amp; Required Clarifications</h2>
<p>To validate this architecture, the following assumptions must be verifie=
d and questions answered by the development team.</p>
<h3 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-4.1KeyAssumptions">4.1 Key Assumptions</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><em>Launcher Auth:</em> The Launcher application performs no internal us=
er authentication and relies solely on underlying file-share permissions.</=
p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Visual Studio Connections:</em> Developers are using Visual Studio t=
o connect directly to production databases, likely via embedded connection =
strings in the Access/Excel artifacts.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>PII Location:</em> PII is present in both the front-end Access/Excel=
 files and the back-end SQL databases.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Tooling Availability:</em> Enterprise Application Support is willing=
 and able to own production deployments using Ansible Automation Platform a=
nd/or MoveIT.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SolutionsArchitectureDocument:LoanProcessAutomationServiceModerni=
zationwithNotes-4.2CriticalQuestionsfortheDevelopmentTeam">4.2 Critical Que=
stions for the Development Team</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Database Connections:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Where are the SQL database connection strings defined today? (e.g., Insi=
de Access VBA, in the Launcher's code, a config file, or a local ODBC DSN?)=
</p></li>
<li>
<p>How are credentials for different environments managed? Are they hard-co=
ded?</p></li>
<li>
<p>What authentication method is used (Windows Integrated, SQL Login)?</p><=
/li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Launcher Configuration:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>How does the Launcher determine which file share path to open? Is this p=
ath hard-coded?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can this path be changed without recompiling the application?</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Artifact Logic:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Confirm if the Excel and Access files contain significant business logic=
 (VBA macros, forms, queries) or if they are primarily data viewers. A demo=
nstration of the most critical logic would be beneficial.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
